    "created_at": "2019-02-03T14:47:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-02-03T14:47:46Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Looking at other hotkeys (production slots for example) the order is clearly left-to-right (i.e. top left, top right, bottom left, bottom right).\r\n\r\nI don't think this can be said for all items, for example the `Record bookmark` or `Jump to bookmark` items are top-to-bottom, whereas the `Slot 01` to `Slot 24` in the `Production Commands` section are left-to-right. \r\n\r\nI find it more comfortable to read descriptions that are in numerical order (slot#, bookmark#) from top to bottom, like columns and rows (rows may continue in the next column). So I would prefer if we used the top-to-bottom order for other items, too (we could break columns by logical groups, like in the `Viewport Commands`).\r\n\r\nRight now we are just inconsistent with the order of items, both in the context of how it is displayed in-game and by which logic it is ordered in the settings."
  },
